===Noun===
'''clove''' (''plural'' [[cloves]])

#A very [[pungent]] [[aromatic]] spice, the unexpanded flower bud of the clove tree ([[Eugenia aromatica]] syn. [[Caryophullus aromatica]]), a native of the Molucca Isles.
#any one of the separate [[bulb]]s that make up the larger bulb of [[garlic]]
#an old English measure of weight, containing 7 pounds; half a [[stone]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1866''': By a statute of 9 Hen. VI. it was ordained that the wey of cheese should contain 32 cloves of 7 lbs. each, i.e. 224 lbs., or 2 cwts. &mdash; James Edwin Thorold Rogers, ''A History of Agriculture and Prices in England'', Volume 1, p. 169.

